Esta aplicação basicamente recebe via terminal, dois valores (digitados pelo usuário), uma String (nome do usuário)
e um Interger (Idade, do usuário). Transformá-os em um arquivo Json e posteriormente, transforma  em um objeto.

 # Cenários:

----- #1:
 Write your name:
 Leandro
 Write your name, using whole numbers:
 39

 Saídas:

 ################# JSON #####################
 {"name":"Leandro","age":39}
 ############################################


 ################# OBJ #####################
 Name: Leandro
 Age: 39
 ############################################

----- #2:
 Write your name:
 Caetano
 Write your name, using whole numbers:
 30

 Saídas:

 ################# JSON #####################
 {"name":"Caetano","age":30}
 ############################################


 ################# OBJ #####################
 Name: Caetano
 Age: 30
 ############################################


 # Desenvolvido com Intellij em Java 17 (Gradle), sistema operacional Ubuntu/Linux

>>>> GITHUB do projeto: https://github.com/CaetanoLeandro/Testes/tree/json-object <<<<<